 The set 
\begin_inset Formula $\bigcup_{t\in[T]}\Xcal_{t}$
\end_inset

 is bounded such that 
\begin_inset Formula $\norm{\xb}_{2}\le1$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $\xb\in\Xcal_{t}$
\end_inset

,
 
\begin_inset Formula $t\in[T]$
\end_inset

,
 and the parameter 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{*}$
\end_inset

 satisfies 
\begin_inset Formula $\norm{\theta_{*}}_{2}\le S$
\end_inset

 for some constant 
\begin_inset Formula $S>0$
\end_inset

 known to the learner.
 
\begin_inset ERT
