\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{assumption}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

[
\end_layout

\end_inset

bounded link function
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

]
\end_layout

\end_inset

 The link function 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

 is twice differentiable over its feasible domain.
 Moreover,
 there exist constants 
\begin_inset Formula $c_{\mu}>0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $L_{\mu}>0$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
c_{\mu}\le\mu'(z)\le L_{\mu},\quad\forall z\in[-S,S].
\]

\end_inset

Consequently,
 the function 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 is strictly convex and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

 is strictly increasing.
 
